          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":42,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"days\":[{\"day_of_week\":0,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Easy long run at 6:27/km. Target 15 km. Keep effort conversational throughout — this is aerobic base building, not racing. Your IT band history means we want a gradual long run build, so resist the urge to push.\"},{\"day_of_week\":1,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest or gentle walking. After Sunday's long run, your legs need time to absorb the stimulus. Rest is where adaptation happens.\"},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run at 6:00–6:27/km. Target 7 km. Keep it genuinely easy — this is recovery-pace aerobic work, not a test run.\"},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"slot_type\":\"CrossTrain\",\"workout_type\":\"CrossTrain\",\"notes\":\"Low-impact cross-training: cycling, swimming, or yoga. 30–40 minutes. Keeps aerobic stimulus without pounding — especially valuable given your IT band history.\"},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"Structured tempo: 2 km warm-up at easy pace, 4 km at threshold pace (4:50/km), 2 km cool-down. Total ~8 km. This mirrors what you nailed on March 16 — build on that confidence.\"},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run at 6:00–6:27/km. Target 6 km. Shake out the legs after yesterday's tempo. Effort should feel like a comfortable conversation.\"},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run at 5:50–6:27/km. Target 6 km. A light aerobic top-up to round out the week. No pressure — just movement.\"}],\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Lee. This opening Base week builds directly on your recent training — you've been running consistently around 33–40 km, so we're stepping up just slightly to 42 km to respect the 10% progression rule. The structure mirrors what's been working for you: a Sunday long run, a midweek tempo, and easy aerobic volume filling the rest. The cross-training day on Wednesday is intentional — given your IT band history, keeping one low-impact day in the week gives that lateral hip chain a break from repetitive loading without losing aerobic fitness. Your tempo pace of 4:50/km is confirmed from your March 16 workout, so you already know what that effort feels like. The goal this week is consistency and confidence — nothing heroic, just solid execution.\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
